{"_id":"prCUShRJDN23mvqV","name":"Defensive Roll","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Starting at 10th level, once per day, a dancer can attempt to avoid a lethal blow. This functions as the thief&rsquo;s advanced talent of the same name.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Defensive Roll (Ex)</p>\n<p>The User can roll with a potentially lethal blow to take less damage from it than she otherwise would. When she would be reduced to 0 or fewer hit points by damage in combat (from a weapon or other blow, not a spell or special ability), the usercan attempt to roll with the damage. To use this ability, the user must attempt a Reflex saving throw (DC = damage dealt). If she succeeds, the thief takes only half damage from the blow; if she fails, she takes full damage. She must be aware of the attack and able to react to it in order to execute her defensive roll; if she is denied her Dexterity bonus to AC, she can&rsquo;t use this ability. Since such damage would not normally allow a character to attempt a Reflex save for half damage, the thief&rsquo;s evasion ability does not apply to the defensive roll.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[["Defensive"]],"actions":[{"_id":"GQ1TFrY4NDOqAlno","name":"Use","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","description":"","tag":"","activation":{"cost":1,"type":"special"},"unchainedAction":{"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""}},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","maxIncrements":1,"minValue":null,"minUnits":""},"uses":{"autoDeductCharges":true,"autoDeductChargesCost":"1","self":{"value":0,"maxFormula":"","per":null},"per":"day","value":1,"maxFormula":"1","max":1},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":"","overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"attackName":"","actionType":null,"attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[],"nonCritParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formulaicAttacks":{"count":{"formula":""},"bonus":{"formula